roach those who have successfully sold their at good market rates and learn from their experience.\u000a\u000a\u201cIndia is already among the top two countries for CER projects. With the global demand for CERs expected to rise significantly in 5-10 years, CERs could be a major contributor to India's export earnings,\u201d says Jaldeep Sodhi, vice-president with Avalon Consulting, which advises in this respect.\u000a\u000aFor selling CERs, commodity futures exchange had launched CER contracts, but it is not liquid as the sellers of these credits are Indian companies, while buyers are overseas entities which cannot buy on Indian exchanges.
