aVPATNA: The rain came down suddenly a day before the New Year eve and the cloud continued to overcast the sky even on New Year, with the occasional dull sun peeping out.Met office sources said here that the rainfall was because of a western disturbance and the sky will clear up by Saturday."Incidentally, the state is witnessing a climatic change for over the last five years. The long cold wave spells are no longer experienced in winter and winters are not that harsh what it used to be," added met office sources.Even the statistics of the Met department reveals that on January 1, 2009, the minimum and maximum temperature recorded was 8.2 and 23.5 degrees Celsius, while the year 2008 recorded 8.5 and 22 degrees Celsius on January 1 and 2007 also had a minimum of 8.3 and a maximum of 23.8 degrees Celsius on this day.Weathermen even attribute this rise in temperature to global warming.However, as deputy director general meteorology (weather forcasting), IMD, Pune, A B Majumdar said, "Variations in weather conditions are normalphenomenon as it depends on many factors. Nothing can be predicted on the basis of short term data analysis. In fact, not very significant change has come to light in terms of global warming."But New Year revellers shrugged off the gloomy damp weather and chill. Partygoers braved the cold weather and celebrated the stroke of midnight.Revellers packed the traditional New Year's eve haunt and all the posh hotels of the city were booked in advance and people had started trooping in from 7 pm onwards.The day was greeted with pop of champagne corks, bursting of crackers and ringing of church bells. Elsewhere around the city, where planned activities went ahead regardless, with revellers wrapped up in warm clothes to brave the chill and cold winds.Almost all the picnic spots, pubs, clubs all were overcrowded.Many parties were organized even on the banks of the Ganga and Ganga diara where arrangements were made for special food and liquor. Some revellers, braving the cold and chill even spent their night partying on the river bank to see the first sun rise of the New Year.In fact, celebrations had started well in advance on December 31 night with people hurrying home and then proceeding to parties, gathering and outing beating away both the weather and recession blues.Special arrangements were made by the district administarion and police to thwart any untoward incident.
