aVCHANDIGARH: At 34.6 degree Celsius, six degrees above normal, the city witnessed the highest temperature of this season so far on Sunday. Giving no respite to residents, mercury has constantly been on the rise since the start of this month. The weatherman has predicted temperature was likely to increase in the coming days.The maximum and minimum temperatures on Monday will be around 35 and 19 degrees. However, the met department has forecast partly cloudy sky during the next 24 hours.There is a marked increase in the highest maximum temperature from March 2009, when it was recorded at 33.2 degrees (incidentally on March 21). In 2007 and 2008, the highest temperature for the month was 35 and 35.4 degree Celsius, respectively.The night temperature on Sunday was reported to be 18.6 degree Celsius, five notches above normal. According to the met department, the maximum and minimum humidity levels were recorded at 86% and 35%, respectively.Surender Paul, met official, said, "This year's temperature is no new phenomenon, as the temperatures had been on the higher sides for the last few years. A factor primarily responsible for the region witnessing high temperatures is too weak western disturbance (WD). Moreover, frequent spells of WD on higher altitudes is depriving the city of cool air." Paul also attributed hotter weather to global warming and climate change. "Residents should get ready to witness higher temperature, as there is no possibility of rain in the coming days," Paul added.
