aVMANGALORE: In a major step aimed at saving electricity, the Palakkad division of Southern Railway has gone in for the use of compact fluorescent lamps (CFL) in a big way. The authorities of the division have replaced all incandescent lamps (ordinary bulbs) and replaced them with CFL in all residential quarters in the division right from Mangalore Central up to Madhukarai under clean development mechanism.A Southern Railway press release here on Saturday stated that as part of the energy saving drive and to reduce energy consumption, the division has embarked on this 'green' drive. When the energy consumption is reduced, carbon emission from the lamp will be less and that will help to reduce the carbon in the environment. Four CFLs are distributed to each quarter and the division has replaced totally about 9,000 CFLs free of cost.Philips Company manufactures these CFLs and they have a life of 10,000 burning hours. It will save around 13,500 units of electric energy per month in Palakkad division. These lamps are provided to use in high usage areas in the home such as living room, kitchen, bedroom and dining room to give maximum benefit. Southern Railway has taken a conscious decision to replace bulbs in all its five divisions and replace them with CFLs.
